OpenCaster 1.0 30/6/2008

Lorenzo Pallara (l.pallara@avalpa.com)

Introduction:
This package is a collection of softwares to generate, process, multiplex and broadcast MPEG2 transport stream format in a Linux system.
It was previously known as JustDVB-It

Manual:
A .pdf manual is available for download at: http://www.avalpa.com/the-key-values/15-free-software/33-opencaster

Features:
- PSI generation (PAT, PMT, NIT, SDT, TDT, AIT, ...)
- Object and data carousel generation (MHP, MHEG5, OTA, ...)
- ffmpeg MPEG2 audio video encoder support 
- FATCAPS DVB-H support 
- IP encapsulation (MPE)
- Scrambling and descrambling (ECD)
- CBR transport stream muxing
- Null packet replacement
- PID filtering
- PID remappaing
- EPG/EIT generation
- Null packet insertion
- Video buffer verifier
- PCR timing verifier
- PES headers analyzer
- MPEG2 video and MPEG2 audio ES header analyzer
- output to DVB-ASI with pci hardware boards
- output to DVB-S, DVB-T and DVB-C with pci hardware boards
